    "last_edit_date" : 1424355382,
    "creation_date" : 1424354815,
    "answer_id" : 28608422,
    "question_id" : 320510,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"http://bndtools.org/index.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Bndtools</a> provides a free JAR viewer plugin for Eclipse.</p>\n\n<p>Add the <a href=\"http://bndtools.org/installation.html#update-site\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Eclipse update site</a> and install only the viewer.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/gNPrK.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 995552,
      "reputation" : 199,
      "user_id" : 1134604,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/MTzLd.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Jose Miguel",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1134604/jose-miguel"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 13,
    "last_activity_date" : 1438167636,
    "creation_date" : 1438167636,
    "answer_id" : 31698573,
    "question_id" : 320510,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Extending Tom Hawtin answer, you can pipe the listing to filter out desired class or files:</p>\n\n<p><code>jar tf my-fat-jar-file.jar | grep filename</code></p>\n\n<p>This should work on bash/zsh and similars, or emacs' eshell.</p>\n\n<p>Additional information: <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/deployment/jar/view.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/deployment/jar/view.html</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 164781,
      "reputation" : 5138,
      "user_id" : 387774,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 74,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/19417323675b23e20322d59559ef80d7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Some Java Guy",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/387774/some-java-guy"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 6,
    "last_activity_date" : 1447411141,
    "creation_date" : 1447411141,
    "answer_id" : 33690835,
    "question_id" : 320510,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you like to see whats inside, simply rename as first option below..</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p><code>F2 &amp; Rename to jarfile.zip</code>    //Use any unzipper...</p></li>\n<li><p><code>jar tvf jarfile.jar</code>    </p></li>\n<li><p><code>jar tf jarfile.jar</code></p></li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3663153,
      "reputation" : 361,
